,
La Moisson en Provence
 
"Last night, we held a very exciting Part I sale of Contemporary Art in New York which brought $74.6* million, leading the market by a comfortable margin," said Mr. Ruprecht.  "Nineteen works sold for over $1 million and the highlight of the evening was Willem de Kooning's , which came in at $11.2 million, above its low estimate of $10.0 million.  Another noteworthy lot was Mark Rothko's , which brought $8.9 million, above its low estimate of $8.0 million."
