Pablo Picasso,
Homme  la pipe
(estimated at $4.7/$6.6 million**) from the artist's series dedicated to the theme of the musketeer.
 
Our summer sale of Old Masters Paintings in London on July 6
th
includes some of the finest offerings of Old Masters Paintings to come to auction in years. The sale is highlighted by Canaletto's
View of the Grand Canal from Palazzo Balbi to the Rialto
(estimate $11/$15 million**) which was one of the first paintings to adorn the Prime Minister's residence at 10 Downing Street in London in the early 1700s. The sale also includes another important Canaletto, his
Venice, The Grand Canal from the Palazzo Flangini to S. Marcuola
which is estimated at $10/$15 million**.
 
About Sotheby's Holdings, Inc.
Sotheby's Holdings, Inc. is the parent company of Sotheby's worldwide auction, private sales and art-related financing activities. The Company operates in 34 countries, with principal salesrooms located in New York and London. The Company also regularly conducts auctions in 13 other salesrooms around the world, including Australia, Hong Kong, France, Italy, the Netherlands, Switzerland and Singapore. Sotheby's Holdings, Inc. is listed on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol BID.
 
