Item 1.01 Entry Into a Material Definitive Agreement
        On January 25, 2007, Sotheby's (the "Company") and Bruno Vinciguerra, entered into a severance agreement, effective as of January 22, 2007 and through December 31, 2008 (the "Severance Agreement"). Mr. Vinciguerra is the Company's newly hired Executive Vice President, Director of New Initiatives.
        Pursuant to the Severance Agreement, if Mr. Vinciguerra's employment is terminated by the Company without Cause or by Mr. Vinciguerra with Good Reason, as such terms are defined in the Severance Agreement, Mr. Vinciguerra will be entitled to (1) accrued but unpaid salary through the termination date, (2) any declared and earned but unpaid bonus for the prior calendar year and (3) a cash payment of $1,000,000. Mr. Vinciguerra may terminate his employment for Good Reason if, among other things, the Company fails to pay him a base salary of not less than $450,000, reduces his annual incentive bonus target below $300,000 or discontinues his participation in the Sotheby's Executive Bonus Plan or a comparable plan. The material terms of the Sotheby's Executive Bonus Plan are described in a Form 8-K filed by the Company on May 10, 2005.
        The Company will file a copy of the Severance Agreement as an exhibit to its Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the quarter ended March 31, 2007.
