Rodin, Aristide Maillol, Fernand Lger, Fernando Botero and Niki de Saint Phalle will highlight the private sale which are on display through mid-April 2007.
 
In London in July, a remarkable collection of 14 watercolours by Britain's greatest watercolourist, J.M.W. Turner, are estimated to bring $20/30 million**. From the collection of Baron Guy Ullens, a Belgian collector who spent over twenty years putting together this series of works that span the first half of the 19 century, the watercolours are made up of beautiful British coastal scenes as well as impressionist views of Switzerland, Germany, France and Italy.
