the Windsors as well as pieces whose inscriptions tell the story of one of the greatest love stories of the 20th century (combined pre-sale estimate of $4.5/6.7 million). 
Also in London, on December 7, Sotheby's will hold a sale of Magnificent Books, Manuscripts and Drawings from the Collection of Frederick, 2nd Lord Hesketh. The most expensive book in the world, Audubon's ($6/10 million) and the most important book in all of English Literature, Shakespeare's ($1.6/2.4 million) are two highlights of the 91 lot sale (total combined pre-sale estimate of $13/16 million).
