Included in our January 2011 Old Master Paintings sale in New York is a monumental work by the Renaissance painter Titian entitled . Significant, multi-figured compositions by Titian are very rare on the market and one has not appeared at auction since 1991 when was acquired by the J. Paul Getty Museum. This rare work has not been seen in public for over thirty years and has a pre-sale estimate of $15/20 million.
