1940s. This sale will mark the first time ever these works have been offered for sale and the paintings have a combined pre-sale estimate in excess of $16 million.
Our June Impressionist and Contemporary Art sales in London are highlighted by one of the most important oils by celebrated Austrian artist Egon Schiele ever to come to the market. of 1914 ranks among just a small number of significant cityscapes by Schiele remaining in private hands. The painting will be offered in the Impressionist and Modern Art evening sale on June 22 and has a pre-sale estimate of $36/50 million.
