Also highlighting our London sales is the Duerckheim Collection, a collection of the most significant and defining German Art of the 1960s and 1970s ever to come to market. The collection features the most important paintings by Georg Baselitz from the 1960s in private hands; an outstanding history of Gerhard Richter's early Photo-paintings; and notably rare and early works by Sigmar Polke, Blinky Palermo, Konrad Lueg, Jrg Immendorff and Eugen Schnebeck, among others. The collection has a pre-sale estimate in excess of $53 million and will be included in the Contemporary Art series.
On July 6, in our London Old Master Paintings sale, we are excited to be able to offer one of the most exceptional Venetian View Paintings ever executed  Francesco Guardi's . Monumental in scale at 45 by 78 inches, it is one of four works that Guardi painted on this grand scale, all executed at around the same time in the late 1760s. Together, these works constitute the pinnacle of Guardi's output as a painter of and they are generally considered to be Guardi's greatest works  the first and fullest expression of the artist's mature style. This painting has a pre-sale estimate of $30 million.
