(b)     each Sotheby Entity may (i) maintain its existing investments in its Subsidiaries and joint ventures as of the Restatement Effective Date, (ii) make investments after the Restatement Effective Date in any Credit Party, or (iii) if such Sotheby Entity is not a Credit Party, make investments after the Restatement Effective Date in any other Sotheby Entity (other than any Immaterial Subsidiary);
(c)     (i) any Borrower may enter into Art Loan/Inventory Joint Ventures and (ii) the Sotheby Entities may make investments after the Restatement Effective Date in joint ventures (other than Art Loan/Inventory Joint Ventures) and other Sotheby Entities (other than any Immaterial Subsidiary) to the extent investments in such other Sotheby Entities are not permitted pursuant to the foregoing
clause (b)
or
